text: Roger Closset (11 February 1933 - 29 October 2020) was a French fencer. He won a silver medal in the team foil event at the 1956 Summer Olympics. He was born in Paris. Closset died in Paris on 29 October 2020 at the age of 87. ==References== Category:1933 births Category:2020 deaths Category:French fencers Category:Olympic silver medalists for France Category:Sportspeople from Paris
